    average of the numbers from a through b (including a and b). 
    Round off the result to the nearest integer and convert that to binary.
    If the first is larger than the second, return -1.
    Example:
    rough_mean(1, 5) => "0b11"
    rough_mean(7, 5) => -1
    rough_mean(10, 20) => "0b1111"
    rough_mean(20, 33) => "0b11010"
    '''
Code  :
def rough_mean(a, b):
    if a > b:
        return -1
    else:
        mean = round((a + b) / 2)
        return bin(mean)
